==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[σχέδιος]]''' (''schedios'') "made suddenly, off-hand", from '''[[σχεδιάζω]]''' (''schediazo'') "to do a thing off-hand".

===Verb===
'''to sketch'''

===Noun===
'''sketch'''
# A quick [[drawing]], often spontaneously produced.
# A short [[dramatic production]].
# (slang used in Ireland) '''keeping sketch''' is to keep a lookout

